album.c scale all the images in different processes at first.
Then in another loop, display each scaled image, ask the user for rotate
information and caption, and do rotation.

albumOneLoop.c work on target images one by one. Scale one image to 10%,
display, ask for rotation, do rotation, and ask for caption. ALl in one loop.

Input: (./album or ./albumOneLoop) + (.jpg/.png/.jpeg files or a folder)

The program will ask the user for the degree to rotate. Y/N is also acceptable.
The default degree is 90. Other input degree will be converted to a
valid degree number.

The program will ask the user for a caption. The default name is the original
name of the file.

Output: album.html